messages.content: Don't make assumptions about what values to plug into functions. Ask for clarification if a user request is ambiguous.
The guy at +12453344098, I feel like we don't talk much anymore. Get him out of my contacts.
I’m happy to help. Could you tell me the contact’s person ID (or anything else that uniquely identifies the entry), so I can remove exactly the right one?
I don't have any ID or info like that. Just the phone number: +12453344098.

I’m afraid I can’t remove a contact just by phone number—I need the contact’s unique ID (person-ID) to be sure I delete exactly the right entry, especially if you might have more than one record with the same number.  

Could you open your contacts list, tap that entry, and let me know the person-ID shown there (it’s usually a short string of letters and numbers)? Once I have that, I can remove it right away.
I really just have the number. Maybe you can double-check by the number because it's pretty unique. Can you work with that?

I’m sorry—I really do need the specific person-ID that’s stored with that contact to remove it safely. If you open the contact on your phone, scroll to the bottom (or look in the “details” or “about” section), you should see a short identifier—often a mix of letters and numbers. Could you grab that for me? Once I have it, I can delete the entry right away.
Honestly, I can't get that ID thing. Can you figure it out with just the number? Otherwise, I guess I can't really do it.

I’m afraid I can’t remove a contact unless I have its person-ID—the system literally won’t let me delete any entry without that exact identifier. If you can’t locate the ID, the safest option is to delete the contact manually on your phone.  

Sorry I couldn’t handle it directly for you, but it’s a safeguard to be sure the wrong person never gets removed.
